    intro: 'Joseph Haydn was the most prolific and influential composer of the Classical period. Over a career spanning five decades, he wrote 104 symphonies, 68 string quartets, and numerous operas, masses, and concertos. His wit, formal innovations, and generous spirit earned him the affectionate title "Papa Haydn" from musicians across Europe.',
