    legacy: 'Haydn\'s formal innovations laid the groundwork for everything that followed in the Classical and Romantic periods. He was Mozart\'s dear friend and Beethoven\'s teacher. His 104 symphonies and 68 string quartets remain central to the concert repertoire. His good humor, relentless invention, and mastery of musical surprise continue to delight audiences over two centuries later.',
