    intro: 'Georges Bizet was a French composer whose brilliant melodic imagination and dramatic instincts produced one of the most beloved operas ever written. Though he died at just 36, his Carmen transformed opera by bringing gritty realism, unforgettable tunes, and psychological depth to the stage, influencing every operatic composer who followed.',
