    funFact: 'Bessie Smith\'s grave in Sharon Hill, Pennsylvania went unmarked for 33 years after her death. In 1970, Janis Joplin — who idolized Smith and modeled her vocal style on hers — and Juanita Green, Smith\'s former housekeeper, split the cost of a proper headstone. It reads: "The Greatest Blues Singer in the World Will Never Stop Singing."',
